----------terraform state - complete
*state lock - when two engineers click on apply at same time it will help whom so ever is 
 clicked apply first, while applying statefile will be locked untill its execution and
 shows the locked/error message to 2nd engineer
*terraform refresh - command is used to see the cuurent state
*terraform state list - commands gives the existing resouces in current state
*terraform state show google_compute_instance.vm2 will give the details of vm2



-----------terraform backend - complete
*we can give the backend bucket to store the state file 
*we can export alredy existing statefile in local to bucket by using command
 terraform init -migrate-state 


-----------terraform drift -completed 
*resource created through terraform [e2-micro]
*changes made through console [e2-small]
*when we click on terraform plan -will override e2-small => e2-micro again
*If we change in our terrform code e2-micro => e2-small
 then terraform plan will show no changes


-------------terraform import -completed
*resouce created through console
*we can import that resouce to terraform statefile to manage
*we have to write the code for that resouce first and then execute the below command

*terraform import google_compute_instance.vm2 projects/<PROJECT_ID>/zones/<ZONE>/instances/vm2

*terraform import google_compute_instance.vm2 projects/my-second-project-501115/zones/us-central1-a/instances/vm2



---------------terraform taint or -replace
*terraform taint is used to mark a resource as damaged or needing replacement in the Terraform state.
*When a resource is tainted, Terraform does not immediately delete or recreate it. Instead, during the next terraform plan or terraform apply, Terraform plans to destroy and recreate that resource.

example--------
  command - terraform taint google_compute_instance.vm2
  output - Resource instance google_compute_instance.vm2 has been marked as tainted.

  command - terraform untaint google_compute_instance.vm2
  output - Resource instance google_compute_instance.vm2 has been successfully untainted.


* terraform plan/apply  will destroy and re-create the vm2